s many of the wizard nukes are AE.<br>
<br>
Now my question is, how would a tank hold multiple agro while allowing players to use long range AE?<br>
<br>
I can't seem to think of ways to do this, and would appreciate any thoughts on the matter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=swipey>Swipey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 560<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/03 6:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little curiousity</span><hr size=1> Maybe you just develop a different tactic than the MA one.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately for Al-Kabor, I can't really think of too many situation where the wider radius and one additional target makes his spells preferable to pillars.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Inferno of Al-Kabor has an efficiency of 1.2 dmg/mana per target, with up to 5 targets.<br>
<br>
Pillar of Frost does 2.35 dmg/mana per target, up to 4.<br>
<br>
Draught of Fire, ~3.4 dmg/mana per target, up to 1. (assumes a damage focus)<br>
<br>
<br>
SO, if one is to use Al kabor, one needs to hit at least 3 targets with it in order to exceed the efficiency of a single target nuke.  (Pillar needs to hit 2 targets to do so.)<br>
<br>
One also needs to NOT be mezzing all foes but one, whom the MA is keeping agro on.  AoE will waken the sleepers, who will then proceed to beat on the wizard.<br>
<br>
This leads to one of two possibilities.<br>
<br>
1) Use Al-Krapors in a group that has no tank.  This begins to look a lot like kiting, though, and pillars will be a lot more efficient.<br>
<br>
2) Run multiple tanks and dont mezz anything.  The wider area of effect on Al-K becomes useful since the 5(!) tanks will not be keeping the 5(!) active foes stacked closely enough to hit them all with pillars.  The problem is, of course, that 5 tanks fighting 5 active foes will require a lot of healing, and probably more than one slower would be advisable, since, by the time a single slower gets to mob #5, its going to have had a lot of time to beat tank #5.  So we'd be talking a raid situation, if everyone is to get exp.  And raid exp is reduced to what?  2/3 normal?  A whole new layer of inefficiency there.<br>
<br>
<br>
