<br>
1) Traditional single group tanking *5 independently operating groups.<br>
<br>
2) 5 groups MA tanking.<br>
<br>
3) 5 groups with 5 tanks operating together.<br>
<br>
<br>
Assumptions (and made up numbers for the sake of demonstration):<br>
Clerics can counter the damage done by one mob over time.  If one cleric is trying to heal the damage done by 2 or more mobs, he will fall behind eventually.<br>
<br>
Enchanters do no damage. They spend their mana either buffing people or debuffing/mezzing mobs.<br>
<br>
Mobs take 3 &quot;units&quot; of damage to kill<br>
<br>
Damage dealers do 0.8 units of damage per minute using single target DDs.<br>
<br>
Tanks 0.6 units of damage per minute.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
SO, using 30 character armies :<br>
<br>
1) Traditional group tanking : <br>
1 Tank, 1 Cleric, 1 chanter, 3 damage dealers.<br>
5 groups operating in parallel but completely independently.  Damage done is 15*0.8 units + 5*0.6 units = 15.0 units per minute.  A rate of 5 mobs per minute.  Individual mobs are alive, awake and doing damage 1 mintue each.<br>
Damage is received at the same rate the clerics can heal it.<br>
<br>
2) Multiple group MA tanking : <br>
1 Tank, 1 Cleric, 5 Enchanters, 23 damage dealers.<br>
All groups assist the tank. All mobs are mezzed except the one engaged.<br>
Damage done is 23*0.8 units + 1*0.6 units = 19 units per minute.  6.33 mobs per minute.  No individual mob is alive, awake and doing damage for more than 9.5 seconds.<br>
Damage recieved is 9.5 seconds * 6.33 mobs, or 1 mob minute's worth, healed by the 1 cleric in the 1 minute.<br>
<br>
3) Multiple group multiple tank, cooperative.<br>
5 Tanks, 5 Clerics, 5 Enchanters, 15 Wizards.<br>
All tanks operate in parallell, engaging one mob at a time.  Wizards use Al-Kabor, though, increasing their damage from 0.8 units to 1.4 each.<br>
Damage done is 15*1.4 units + 5*0.6 units = 24.0 Units per minute.  8 mobs per minute.  Individual mobs live 5/8 of a minute.<br>
Damage received is 8 mobs doing damage for 5/8 minutes, a total of 5 mob minutes worth, which is healed by the 5 clerics.<br>
<br>
<br>
So.. <br>
Traditional single group tanking : 5 exp, evenly divided.<br>
Multiple group MA tanking : 6.33 exp, not evenly divided*<br>
Multiple group multiple tanking : 8.0 exp, not evenly divided*<br>
<br>
* or, evenly divided, if one forms a raid, but then a 2/3 multiplier is aplied, making MA tanking slightly less efficient than single grouping, and Mass Kaboring only slightly more efficient.  And getting that many wizards would be a pain.<br>
